<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-912-566  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 912 566.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Vision Graphics andamp; Image Processing  Oct 1989 v48 n1p50(30).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Modeling sensors: toward automatic generation of objectrecognition program. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ikeuchi, Katsushi; Kanade, Takeo.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Object recognition is important in many practical vision problems.andO;Prior knowledge of the objects' shapes, sizes and/or reflectiveproperties is usually available.andP;  Model-based vision uses priorknowledge of objects to guide the recognition process for enhancedefficiency and reliability.andP;  Fast extraction and organization ofthe relevant knowledge of an object and turning it into a visionprogram systematically are critical issues in the development ofmodel-based vision systems.andP;  Among the components required forautomatic generation of object recognition programs are objectmodels, sensor models, strategy generation and program generation.andO;Sensor modeling and its relationship to strategy generation isstudied, and a general framework for incorporating explicitlysensor models that govern the relationship between object modelsand object appearances is presented.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Object RecognitionTheoretical ResearchTechnologyNew TechniqueProgram GeneratorsSensorsModelingAlgorithm AnalysisComputer Vision.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   Object-appearances. (chart)Summary of sensors. (table)Feature configuration space. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>